    "body": "Ref: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39889#discussion_r3272050312\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n`vim.pos.cursor(vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf(win), vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(win))` is too verbose to create a cursor position of a window, but it is a common use case.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nOverload `vim.pos.cursor()`, so that it accepts `win` as an argument when `pos` is omitted.\r\n\r\nI also packed `row` and `col` before returning them, so that `pos.to_cursor()` matched the parameter of `pos.cursor`.",
    "closed_at": "2026-06-14T16:42:52Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40087#discussion_r3409873635"
                },
