                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/40087"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3409873635"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This is a cool approach. I can't think of any problems with it. All of the `pos.<kind>()` are by their nature somewhat special-case. \n\nExcept that we made `buf` consistently the first param, which seems helpful. Maybe we should continue insisting on that, and consider instead : \n\n    pos = vim.pos.cursor(nil, {win=0})\n\nor \n\n    pos = vim.pos.cursor({win=0})\n\nbut meanwhile let's try this out.",
            "commit_id": "f79999270ed30c85a13e1f06c845a82939918a28",
            "created_at": "2026-06-14T16:38:03Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -4503,15 +4503,24 @@ by |vim.Pos| objects.\n cursor({buf}, {pos})                                        *vim.pos.cursor()*\n     Creates a new |vim.Pos| from cursor position (see |api-indexing|).\n \n+    If {pos} is omitted, the first argument is treated as {win} instead of\n+    {buf}, and the current cursor position of {win} is used.",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40087#discussion_r3409873635",
